Progress in reducing the malaria burden in Africa has stalled, which has raised concerns about the impact of climate change on malaria eradication efforts. Despite extensive research on the links between climate and malaria, there is still no consensus on the specific impacts of future climate change scenarios on malaria transmission, which complicates response strategies.

